HB 381 Original 2026 Regular Session Jordan
Abstract: Makes a company ineligible for the High Impact Jobs Program if a certain
number of its employees qualify for SNAP benefits.
Present law provides for the High Impact Jobs Program.
Present law provides for the eligibility of companies in the High Impact Jobs Program.
Proposed law adds that a company that has 20% or more of La. employees who qualify for
the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP), shall be ineligible for participation
in the program.
Proposed law further provides that LED shall coordinate with the La. Dept. of Health to
access the required information to implement proposed law.
(Adds R.S. 51:2771(C)(3))
